properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 10 at 11:37PM PST until February 11 at 10:32AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Cedar River Near Landsburg affecting King County
Cedar River At Renton affecting King County
Green River Near Auburn affecting King County

The rivers will continue to slowly recede through Tuesday.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Cedar River Near Landsburg
* Until Tuesday morning.
* At 11:00 PM Monday the stage was 5.8 feet.
* Flood stage is 5.7 feet.
* Minor flooding is occurring.
* Forecast...The river has crested and will continue to fall to below
flood stage early Tuesday morning.
* Impact...At 5.7 feet, the Cedar River will cause flooding from
Landsburg downstream through Maplewood. Swift waters will flood
roads and some residential areas, especially in Maple Valley.
Flooding threatens Beyers Road. A stage of 5.7 feet on the Cedar
River corresponds roughly to a phase 4 flood in the King County
flood system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.

NWSheadline: Flood Warning extended until Tuesday morning
